'''Aria Yousefi''' ({{langx|fa|آریا یوسفی}}; born 22 April 2002) is an Iranian [[Association football|football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] who plays for [[Sepahan F.C.|Sepahan]] in the [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].

==Career==
Yousefi was born in [[Bandar-e Mahshahr]], and is a youth product of [[Naft Ahvaz F.C.|Naft Ahvaz]] and [[Sepahan F.C.|Sepahan]]. He debuted in the [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] with Sepahan in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beytoote.com/sport/athletic/biography2-aria-yousefi.html|title=بیوگرافی آریا یوسفی، فوتبالیست ماهشهری|website=www.beytoote.com|access-date=13 April 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Yousefi debuted with the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]] in a friendly 2–1 win over [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] on 5 January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/37863/Iran_Burkina_Faso.html|title=Iran vs. Burkina Faso|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com|access-date=13 April 2024}}</ref> He was included in the final squad in the Iranian senior team to compete for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] in [[Qatar]] in January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footballi.net/news/r/850617/%D8%AF%D9%84%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%84-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D9%88%D8%B4-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86-%DB%8C%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%81%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%AD%D8%B3%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%82%DB%8C|title=دلایل ملیپوش شدن یوسفی از زبان محمدحسین میثاقی!|date=1 January 2024|website=فوتبالی|access-date=13 April 2024}}</ref>

On the 8th of September 2025, in a CAFA Nations Cup match against Uzbekistan, Yousefi obtained a red card and was sent off. It was the first red card of his international career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teammelli.com/ten-man-iran-collapses-at-the-death-handing-uzbekistan-historic-cafa-cup-triumph/|title=Ten-Man Iran Collapses at the Death, Handing Uzbekistan Historic CAFA Cup Triumph|date=8 September 2025|website=Team Melli|access-date=16 February 2025}}</ref>

